Ooyoko River is a canal, that's why.

127
00:08:40,248 --> 00:08:43,548
A local feudal lord made this by order of the Edo Shogunate.

128
00:08:49,648 --> 00:08:50,848
Amazing.

129
00:08:54,348 --> 00:08:55,848
That brat...

130
00:08:57,548 --> 00:08:58,948
Don't you get in my way, brat!

131
00:08:58,948 --> 00:09:00,348
Lower your head!

132
00:09:03,948 --> 00:09:04,948
That was close!

133
00:09:05,948 --> 00:09:08,848
During high tide, water level rises, that the bridge gets so low,

134
00:09:08,848 --> 00:09:11,948
