00:10:40,648 --> 00:10:42,748
M has entered Heikyu River.

147
00:10:43,848 --> 00:10:46,748
The briefcase is on the roof of the cruiser.

148
00:10:46,748 --> 00:10:49,248
What? Keep your eyes on the cruiser!

149
00:10:49,248 --> 00:10:50,348
Roger!

150
00:10:50,348 --> 00:10:51,848
I'll go get the car.

151
00:11:31,348 --> 00:11:33,348
The briefcase is gone!

152
00:11:40,461 --> 00:11:42,461
The briefcase is gone!

153
00:11:44,227 --> 00:11:46,427
Conan? What brings you here?

154
00:11:46,427 --> 00:11:47,927
The briefcase is gone!

155
00:11:47,927 --> 00:11:49,227
-What? -What?

156
00:11:49,227 --> 00:11:51,527
Bad news! We've got to contact the inspector.

157
00:11:54,727 --> 00:11:55,727
Darn!

158
00:11:57,027 --> 00:11:58,527
Pops!

159
00:11:58,527 --> 00:12:01,327
Pops! We've got trouble!

160
00:12:01,327 --> 00:12:03,127
Shut up! Don't bother me!

161
00:12:03,127 --> 00:12:05,727
The briefcase on the roof is gone!

162
00:12:05,727 --> 00:12:06,727
What?

163
00:12:09,827 --> 00:12:12,527
It's gone! It's gone! It's gone! It's gone!

164
00:12:12,527 --> 00:12:14,927
Hey, look out, sir!

165
00:12:14,927 --> 00:12:18,127
The briefcase is gone!

166
00:12:21,827 --> 00:12:22,927
Mr. Mouri!

167
00:12:24,627 --> 00:12:26,527
How'd he do it?

168
00:12:26,527 --> 00:12:30,727
How on earth the culprit take the briefcase?

169
00:12:36,827 --> 00:12:39,327
"Mouri Detective Agency"

170
00:12:41,027 --> 00:12:42,027
In other words,

171
00:12:42,027 --> 00:12:44,827
