172
00:12:44,827 --> 00:12:48,427
To put the briefcase on the roof after entering Ooyoko River?

173
00:12:48,427 --> 00:12:49,427
Yes...

174
00:12:52,527 --> 00:12:53,527
Yes.

175
00:12:53,527 --> 00:12:55,927
You got nothing, no directions, after that?

176
00:12:55,927 --> 00:12:56,927
No.

177
00:12:58,927 --> 00:13:03,227
And, by the time you realized it, the briefcase was gone?

178
00:13:03,227 --> 00:13:06,227
Yes, sir. Because he told me to go back to my seat

179
00:13:06,227 --> 00:13:08,327
and wait for further contact.

180
00:13:08,327 --> 00:13:09,727
What a shame.

181
00:13:09,727 --> 00:13:11,327
And, Conan...

182
00:13:11,327 --> 00:13:14,427
When did you last see the briefcase?

183
00:13:14,427 --> 00:13:16,027
Well...

184
00:13:16,027 --> 00:13:19,027
Over here. Totomi Bridge here.

185
00:13:19,027 --> 00:13:23,727
The last we saw of it was Shiomi Bridge here.

186
00:13:23,727 --> 00:13:29,427
And you realized that the briefcase was gone at Hamazono Bridge here.

187
00:13:29,427 --> 00:13:33,927
In other words, the culprit would have had to take the briefcase

188
00:13:33,927 --> 00:13:36,627
from somewhere between Heikyu Bridge and Hamazono Bridge.

189
00:13:36,627 --> 00:13:39,727
Mr. Mouri, was there anything you noticed?

190
00:13:41,827 --> 00:13:44,227
I'm very sorry.

191
00:13:44,227 --> 00:13:46,727
It seems like I've caught a cold

192
00:13:46,727 --> 00:13:48,827
That's obvious.

193
00:13:48,827 --> 00:13:49,927
Oh, right.

194
00:13:49,927 --> 00:13:53,827
Bback then, I heard a metallic sound of something banging onto steel.

195
00:13:53,827 --> 00:13:56,127
A metallic sound?

196
00:13:56,127 --> 00:13:59,927
If I remember correctly, somewhere around here...

197
00:13:59,927 --> 00:14:02,527
I think it was a small bridge.

198
00:14:02,527 --> 00:14:06,327
There were two small boats anchored under the bridge.

199
00:14:06,327 --> 00:14:08,227
Were there people on the boats?

200
00:14:08,227 --> 00:14:10,327
No, no one.

201
00:14:10,327 --> 00:14:13,627
I heard the sound when the skipper veered the cruiser to the right

202
00:14:13,627 --> 00:14:16,227
to avoid the boats and sailed under the bridge

203
00:14:17,527 --> 00:14:18,927
What was that?

204
00:14:18,927 --> 00:14:20,727
Maybe we hit a bridge?

205
00:14:20,727 --> 00:14:22,127
No way.

206
00:14:22,127 --> 00:14:24,327
If so the cruiser should sway more.

207
00:14:24,327 --> 00:14:25,927
I see.

208
00:14:26,927 --> 00:14:29,427
That was probably Shigure Bridge.

209
00:14:29,427 --> 00:14:32,327
When we were watching from Shiomi Bridge,

210
00:14:32,327 --> 00:14:34,727
Heikyu Bridge was in sight,

211
00:14:34,727 --> 00:14:36,627
but there were no boats.

212
00:14:36,627 --> 00:14:40,027
Besides, Ishihama Bridge just ahead of Shigure Bridge

213
00:14:40,027 --> 00:14:42,227
has a water gate right behind it.

214
00:14:42,227 --> 00:14:45,927
I don't think you'll get the impression of it being a small bridge.

215
00:14:45,927 --> 00:14:47,427
I see.

216
00:14:47,427 --> 00:14:50,027
The next bridge is already Hamazono Bridge

217
00:14:50,027 --> 00:14:51,927
so I'm sure that there's no doubt that the metallic sound

218
00:14:51,927 --> 00:14:54,927
was heard at Shigure Bridge.

219
00:14:54,927 --> 00:14:57,727
But, I wonder if that metallic sound

220
00:14:57,727 --> 00:15:00,027
has anything to do with the case we're dealing with now?

221
00:15:00,027 --> 00:15:02,027
Inspector Megure.

222
00:15:02,027 --> 00:15:05,427
This was found near the water of Heikyu Bridge.

223
00:15:06,627 --> 00:15:07,827
That's...

224
00:15:10,027 --> 00:15:11,327
Mr. Mouri,

225
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:14,027
is this the briefcase?

226
00:15:15,027 --> 00:15:16,827
No mistake, that's it!

227
00:15:16,827 --> 00:15:19,627
Open it and confirm the inside too.

228
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:21,227
May take a look?

229
00:15:28,727 --> 00:15:33,827
Pops, the cloth of the lid of the briefcase is ripped.

230
00:15:33,827 --> 00:15:35,027
What?

231
00:15:36,027 --> 00:15:37,527
According to forensics,

232
00:15:37,527 --> 00:15:38,927
just as Conan has mentioned,

233
00:15:38,927 --> 00:15:40,927
the inside of the lid has been ripped off,

234
00:15:40,927 --> 00:15:42,327
and further inside,

235
00:15:42,327 --> 00:15:45,727
