236
00:15:45,727 --> 00:15:46,727
What?

237
00:15:46,727 --> 00:15:49,227
Then, does that mean that the culprit used whatever it was

238
00:15:49,227 --> 00:15:51,427
that was rigged on to it, to take the briefcase?

239
00:15:51,427 --> 00:15:54,627
No, we don't know that yet...

240
00:15:57,027 --> 00:15:58,427
Mr. Mouri?

241
00:15:58,427 --> 00:15:59,827
Dad.

242
00:15:59,827 --> 00:16:01,027
Inspector.

243
00:16:01,027 --> 00:16:04,527
I've figured out how the culprit had taken the briefcase.

244
00:16:04,527 --> 00:16:05,627
Mouri.

245
00:16:05,627 --> 00:16:07,927
He's not nasal anymore?

246
00:16:07,927 --> 00:16:09,127
Rats.

247
00:16:09,127 --> 00:16:12,027
It flashed upon me, that my nose suddenly unplugged.

248
00:16:13,327 --> 00:16:15,727
Never mind that, but inspector...

249
00:16:15,727 --> 00:16:18,627
The culprit probably used a strong magnet.

250
00:16:18,627 --> 00:16:20,327
Magnet?

251
00:16:20,327 --> 00:16:22,127
The characteristic of Ooyoko River

252
00:16:22,127 --> 00:16:25,227
is that the water level greatly changes during high and low tide.

253
00:16:25,227 --> 00:16:28,627
The distance between the bridge becomes very narrow.

254
00:16:28,627 --> 00:16:30,427
The culprit probably checked the time

255
00:16:30,427 --> 00:16:34,027
that the water level rises beforehand

256
00:16:34,027 --> 00:16:38,527
and rigged a strong magnet onto the lid of the briefcase.

257
00:16:38,527 --> 00:16:40,727
By doing so, when the cruiser sails

258
00:16:40,727 --> 00:16:43,027
under the extremely narrow space of the bridge...

259
00:16:44,727 --> 00:16:46,327
Wait a minute.

260
00:16:46,327 --> 00:16:48,027
There are many bridges,

261
00:16:48,027 --> 00:16:50,227
so there's no way of telling which bridge it would attach too, no?

262
00:16:50,227 --> 00:16:56,027
No. So the culprit used an electromagnet

263
00:16:56,027 --> 00:16:58,127
that would generates magnetic force at his convenience.

