00:17:02,627 --> 00:17:04,927
a coil around a magnetic material generates magnetic force

266
00:17:04,927 --> 00:17:07,227
only when electric current is applied to the coil.

267
00:17:07,227 --> 00:17:10,427
The culprit probably embedded in the lid of the briefcase

268
00:17:10,427 --> 00:17:13,027
an iron bar wrapped with coil and a battery.

269
00:17:13,027 --> 00:17:17,727
Then, he installed a remote control switch that enables remote operation.

270
00:17:39,927 --> 00:17:42,527
Finally, after everyone left,

271
00:17:42,527 --> 00:17:45,227
he switched off the power and retrieved the briefcase.

272
00:17:48,127 --> 00:17:51,327
Okay! Based on Mouri's deduction,

273
00:17:51,327 --> 00:17:54,927
re-investigate the vicinity of Ooyoko River and Heikyu River.

274
00:17:54,927 --> 00:17:56,027
-Yes, sir. -Yes sir.

275
00:17:59,027 --> 00:18:00,827
Geez, dad...

276
00:18:00,827 --> 00:18:04,527
Your cold will get worse if you sleep in a place like this.

277
00:18:04,527 --> 00:18:08,527
I wonder why the culprit designated pops?

278
00:18:08,527 --> 00:18:10,027
I wonder...

279
00:18:10,027 --> 00:18:13,727
The papers of the cases that pops handled are still here, aren't they?

280
00:18:13,727 --> 00:18:16,727
Yeah, I think they're filed.

281
00:18:16,727 --> 00:18:19,827
Maybe we'll be able to figure something out by looking at those files.

282
00:18:21,927 --> 00:18:27,227
Maybe that culprit is somebody who has a grudge against dad?

283
00:18:29,027 --> 00:18:30,627
Could be.

284
00:18:41,727 --> 00:18:45,627
Is anything wrong, Ran?

285
00:18:45,627 --> 00:18:47,927
No, it's nothing.

286
00:18:49,627 --> 00:18:51,327
I was just thinking that if it were Shinichi,

287
00:18:51,327 --> 00:18:54,227
he would immediately solve a problem like this.

288
00:18:56,127 --> 00:18:57,727
Don't worry.

289
00:18:57,727 --> 00:18:59,827
I'll solve it for you.

290
00:19:01,227 --> 00:19:03,527
Just as would be expected of a member of the Youth Detective Squad.

291
00:19:03,527 --> 00:19:06,827
Then, shall we solve it, the two of us, in place of dad?

292
00:19:06,827 --> 00:19:07,827
Yes.

293
00:19:09,027 --> 00:19:11,727
The keyword is New Image.

294
00:19:11,727 --> 00:19:15,627
I'm sure that it has something to do with New Image and pops.

295
00:20:16,627 --> 00:20:20,527
"Mouri Detective Agency"

296
00:20:36,727 --> 00:20:37,927
I found it.

297
00:20:37,927 --> 00:20:40,527
Isn't this it?

298
00:20:40,527 --> 00:20:42,227
This.

299
00:20:42,227 --> 00:20:45,027
Satoshi Nishizawa, 32 years old.

300
00:20:45,027 --> 00:20:49,927
Mechanic engineer for New Image, an import car dealer.

301
00:20:49,927 --> 00:20:53,627
There is a request from Kaori Ida, 37 years old,

302
00:20:53,627 --> 00:20:57,127
to find the person who has been stalking her.

303
00:20:57,127 --> 00:20:58,527
As a result of the investigation,

304
00:20:58,527 --> 00:21:00,527
it becomes apparent that the stalker is Nishizawa.

305
00:21:00,527 --> 00:21:03,827
There was a court order prohibiting him from going close to her.

306
00:21:03,827 --> 00:21:07,027
Thus, he was fired.

307
00:21:07,027 --> 00:21:09,527
This is a case of 2 months ago.

308
00:21:09,527 --> 00:21:10,727
What's his address?

309
00:21:10,727 --> 00:21:12,727
Fukagawa, Koto ward.

310
00:21:12,727 --> 00:21:14,627
Isn't this near Ooyoko River?

311
00:21:14,627 --> 00:21:15,627
Yes.

312
00:22:50,027 --> 00:22:51,027
This way.

313
00:22:55,627 --> 00:22:57,427
It's that apartment, isn't it?

314
00:22:57,427 --> 00:22:58,427
Yes.

315
00:23:03,127 --> 00:23:06,427
Mr. Nishizawa. Are you in?

316
00:23:06,427 --> 00:23:08,027
Mr. Nishizawa!

317
00:23:11,027 --> 00:23:12,627
It seems he's not in.

318
00:23:12,627 --> 00:23:13,627
Yes.

319
00:23:16,927 --> 00:23:18,027
It's open.

320
00:23:21,327 --> 00:23:24,127
Mr. Nishizawa, aren't you home?

321
00:23:25,227 --> 00:23:26,927
Mr. Nishizawa!

322
00:23:31,527 --> 00:23:32,727
Conan.

323
00:23:41,827 --> 00:23:43,827
No, Conan.

324
00:23:43,827 --> 00:23:46,127
You shouldn't go into other people's houses without permission.

325
00:23:58,427 --> 00:23:59,927
Wait, Ran.

326
00:23:59,927 --> 00:24:01,227
Look.

327
00:24:01,227 --> 00:24:03,227
It's all the way up to the brim of the bath tub.

328
00:24:03,227 --> 00:24:05,027
Nishizawa committed suicide.

329
00:24:05,027 --> 00:24:08,327
Even if it may not be something too convenient for you?

330
00:24:08,327 --> 00:24:11,327
I can see it wasn't an easy job. So, keep it.

331
00:24:11,327 --> 00:24:14,727
Well, I'm sure we'll eventually come up with an answer.

332
00:24:14,727 --> 00:24:17,627
But, no yellow flower looks to be in sight.

333
00:24:17,627 --> 00:24:19,327
I have someone in mind.

334
00:24:19,327 --> 00:24:20,627
You mean Nishizawa didn't do it

335
00:24:20,627 --> 00:24:22,427
and he didn't commit suicide?

336
00:24:22,427 --> 00:24:23,727
Next Conan,

337
00:24:23,727 --> 00:24:27,927
"Sumida River Night Cherry Blossom Route (Part 2)"

338
00:24:43,727 --> 00:24:45,627
Next Conan's Hint:

339
00:24:45,627 --> 00:24:48,027
"Flower viewing boat".

340
00:24:48,027 --> 00:24:49,527
Dad, are you okay?

341
00:24:50,527 --> 00:24:51,527
I guess he'd like to run to see cherry blossoms,

342
00:24:51,527 --> 00:24:52,927
but the only thing that's running is his nose.

